+{"goal":"Start","pass1":{"system":"# Goal Builder\n\nYou are the PLang compiler. Map each step in a goal to engine actions.\n\n## How the Engine Works\n\nThe engine has **modules** (namespaces) with **action classes**. Each action class has properties and a \u0060Run()\u0060 method.\n\nYour job: for each step, produce \u0060{module, action, parameters}\u0060 where:\n- \u0060module\u0060 = namespace (output, file, goal, condition, variable, etc.)\n- \u0060action\u0060 = class name (write, read, call, if, set, etc.)\n- \u0060parameters\u0060 = list of \u0060{name, value, type}\u0060 matching the class properties\n\nThe engine does: find class \u2192 set properties \u2192 call Run().\n\n## Available Actions\n\nNotation: %var% = value must be a %variable% reference | type(a|b) = valid values | = val is default, param is optional\n\n\n# module\n\n## remove [no-cache]\n  { Name: string }\n\n\n## add [no-cache]\n  { Path: string, Namespace: string? }\n\n\n\n# goal\n\n## return [no-cache]\n  { Data: this?, Depth: int = 1 }\n\n\n## call\n  { GoalName: goal.call, Actor: this?(user|service|system) }\n\n\n\n# variable\n\n## get\n  { Name: %var% string }\n\n\n## remove [no-cache]\n  { Name: %var% string }\n\n\n## clear [no-cache]\n  (no parameters)\n\n\n## set [no-cache]\n  { Name: %var% string, Value: this, Type: string?, AsDefault: bool = false }\n\n\n## exists\n  { Name: %var% string }\n\n\n\n# provider\n\n## setDefault [no-cache]\n  { Name: string, Type: string? }\n\n\n## remove [no-cache]\n  { Name: string, Type: string? }\n\n\n## load [no-cache]\n  { Path: string?, Name: string? }\n\n\n## list [no-cache]\n  { Type: string? }\n\n\n\n# output\n\n## write [no-cache]\n  { Data: this, Channels: this }\n  e.g. \u0060write out \u0027hello\u0027\u0060 \u2192 Data=hello\n  e.g. \u0060write trace \u0027debug info\u0027\u0060 \u2192 Data=debug info, Properties={channel: trace}\n\n\n\n# settings\n\n## get\n  { Key: string }\n\n\n## remove [no-cache]\n  { Key: string }\n\n\n## set [no-cache]\n  { Key: string, Value: object? }\n\n\n\n# list\n\n## add [no-cache]\n  { ListName: %var% string, Value: object?, AtIndex: int = -1 }\n\n\n## split\n  { Value: string, Separator: string = \u0022,\u0022, RemoveEmpty: bool = false }\n\n\n## set [no-cache]\n  { ListName: %var% string, Index: int, Value: object? }\n\n\n## range\n  { Start: int, End: int, Step: int = 1 }\n\n\n## last\n  { ListName: %var% string }\n\n\n## join\n  { ListName: %var% string, Separator: string = \u0022,\u0022 }\n\n\n## reverse [no-cache]\n  { ListName: %var% string }\n\n\n## sort [no-cache]\n  { ListName: %var% string, Descending: bool = false }\n\n\n## unique\n  { ListName: %var% string }\n\n\n## remove [no-cache]\n  { ListName: %var% string, Value: object?, AtIndex: int = -1 }\n\n\n## count\n  { ListName: %var% string }\n\n\n## flatten\n  { ListName: %var% string }\n\n\n## indexof\n  { ListName: %var% string, Value: object? }\n\n\n## contains\n  { ListName: %var% string, Value: object? }\n\n\n## first\n  { ListName: %var% string }\n\n\n## get\n  { ListName: %var% string, Index: int }\n\n\n\n# app\n\n## run\n  { GoalName: goal.call?, Step: this?, Action: this?, Actor: this?(user|service|system) }\n\n\n\n# crypto\n\n## verify [no-cache]\n  { Data: this, Hash: string, Algorithm: string = \u0022keccak256\u0022 }\n  e.g. \u0060verify %content% against %hash%, write to %isValid\u0060 \u2192 Data=%content%, Hash=%hash%, Algorithm=keccak256\n  e.g. \u0060verify %data% against %hash% with sha256, write to %isValid\u0060 \u2192 Data=%data%, Hash=%hash%, Algorithm=sha256\n\n\n## hash [no-cache]\n  { Data: this, Algorithm: string = \u0022keccak256\u0022 }\n  e.g. \u0060hash %content%, write to %hash\u0060 \u2192 Data=%content%, Algorithm=keccak256\n  e.g. \u0060hash %data% with sha256, write to %hash\u0060 \u2192 Data=%data%, Algorithm=sha256\n\n\n\n# mock\n\n## verify [no-cache]\n  { Mock: mockhandle, ExpectedCount: int, Message: string? }\n\n\n## reset [no-cache]\n  { Mock: mockhandle? }\n\n\n## intercept [no-cache]\n  { ActionPattern: string, ReturnValue: object?, GoalToCall: goal.call?, Parameters: dict\u003Cstring,object\u003E? }\n\n\n\n# condition\n\n## compare\n  { Left: this?, Operator: operator(==|!=|\u003E|\u003C|\u003E=|\u003C=|contains|startswith|endswith|in|isempty|and|or), Right: this? }\n  e.g. \u0060compare %a% \u003E %b%, write to %isGreater\u0060 \u2192 Left=%a%, Operator=\u003E, Right=%b%\n  e.g. \u0060compare %status% == \u0027active\u0027, write to %isActive\u0060 \u2192 Left=%status%, Operator===, Right=active\n\n\n## if\n  { Left: this?, Operator: operator(==|!=|\u003E|\u003C|\u003E=|\u003C=|contains|startswith|endswith|in|isempty|and|or), Right: this?, Negate: bool = false, Step: this }\n  e.g. \u0060if %count% \u003E 0\n    - call ProcessItems\u0060 \u2192 Left=%count%, Operator=\u003E, Right=0\n  e.g. \u0060if %name% equals \u0027Alice\u0027\n    - write \u0027Hello Alice\u0027\u0060 \u2192 Left=%name%, Operator===, Right=Alice\n  e.g. \u0060if %x% \u003E 5 set %b% = 4, else set %b% = 0\u0060 \u2192 Left=%x%, Operator=\u003E, Right=5 (condition orchestrates then/else actions in same step)\n\n\n\n# cache\n\n## store [no-cache]\n  { Step: this, Data: this }\n\n\n## check [no-cache]\n  { Step: this }\n\n\n\n# math\n\n## abs\n  { Value: object }\n\n\n## multiply\n  { A: object, B: object }\n\n\n## floor\n  { Value: object }\n\n\n## min\n  { A: object, B: object }\n\n\n## round\n  { Value: object, Decimals: int = 0 }\n\n\n## ceiling\n  { Value: object }\n\n\n## power\n  { Base: object, Exponent: object }\n\n\n## max\n  { A: object, B: object }\n\n\n## add\n  { A: object, B: object }\n\n\n## random\n  { Min: int = 0, Max: int = 100 }\n\n\n## divide\n  { A: object, B: object }\n\n\n## sqrt\n  { Value: object }\n\n\n## modulo\n  { A: object, B: object }\n\n\n## subtract\n  { A: object, B: object }\n\n\n\n# llm\n\n## query\n  { Messages: list\u003Cllmmessage\u003E, Tools: list\u003Cgoal.call\u003E?, OnToolCall: goal.call?, OnValidateResponse: goal.call?, OnStream: goal.call?, Schema: string?, Format: string?, Model: string?, ContinuePreviousConversation: bool = false, Temperature: double = 0, MaxTokens: int = 4000, MaxToolCalls: int = 10, MaxValidationRetries: int = 0, Cache: bool = true }\n  e.g. \u0060system: analyze sentiment\n  user: %comment%\n  schema: {sentiment: string}\n  write to %result\u0060 \u2192 Messages=[{Role=system, Text=analyze sentiment}, {Role=user, Text=%comment%}], Schema={sentiment: string}\n  e.g. \u0060system: you are a helpful assistant\n  user: %question%\n  tools:\n    GetWeather, gets weather for a city, %city%(string), parallel\n  write to %answer\u0060 \u2192 Messages=[{Role=system, Text=you are a helpful assistant}, {Role=user, Text=%question%}], Tools=[{Name=GetWeather, Description=gets weather for a city, Parameters=[{Name=city, Type=string}], Parallel=true}]\n\n\n\n# http\n\n## request\n  { Url: string, Method: httpmethod = GET, Body: object?, Headers: dict\u003Cstring,object\u003E?, ContentType: string = \u0022application/json\u0022, Encoding: string = \u0022utf-8\u0022, TimeoutInSec: int = 30, Unsigned: bool = false, SignOptions: sign?, OnStream: goal.call?, StreamAs: streamformat? }\n\n\n## download [no-cache]\n  { Url: string, SaveTo: string, IfExists: fileexists = Error, Headers: dict\u003Cstring,object\u003E?, TimeoutInSec: int = 30, Unsigned: bool = false, SignOptions: sign?, OnProgress: goal.call? }\n\n\n## upload [no-cache]\n  { Url: string, Content: object, Method: httpmethod = POST, Headers: dict\u003Cstring,object\u003E?, Encoding: string = \u0022utf-8\u0022, TimeoutInSec: int = 30, Unsigned: bool = false, SignOptions: sign?, As: contentas?, OnProgress: goal.call? }\n\n\n## configure [no-cache]\n  { TimeoutInSec: int?, BaseUrl: string?, DefaultHeaders: dict\u003Cstring,object\u003E?, ContentType: string?, Encoding: string?, Unsigned: bool?, FollowRedirects: bool?, MaxRedirects: int?, Default: bool = false }\n\n\n\n# file\n\n## delete [no-cache]\n  { Path: path, IgnoreIfNotFound: bool = false, Recursive: bool = false }\n  e.g. \u0060delete file.txt\u0060 \u2192 Path=file.txt\n  e.g. \u0060delete %path%, ignore if not found\u0060 \u2192 Path=%path%, IgnoreIfNotFound=true\n  e.g. \u0060delete temp/, recursive\u0060 \u2192 Path=temp/, Recursive=true\n\n\n## copy [no-cache]\n  { Source: path, Destination: path, Overwrite: bool = false, IncludeSubfolders: bool = true }\n  e.g. \u0060copy file.txt to backup/file.txt\u0060 \u2192 Source=file.txt, Destination=backup/file.txt\n  e.g. \u0060copy %source% to %dest%, overwrite\u0060 \u2192 Source=%source%, Destination=%dest%, Overwrite=true\n\n\n## read\n  { Path: path, ResolveVariables: bool = false }\n  e.g. \u0060read file.txt, write to %content\u0060 \u2192 Path=file.txt\n  e.g. \u0060read %path%, write to %data\u0060 \u2192 Path=%path%\n  e.g. \u0060read file.txt, load vars, write to %content\u0060 \u2192 Path=file.txt, ResolveVariables=true\n\n\n## exists\n  { Path: path }\n  returns: { Raw: string, Absolute: string, Relative: string, Extension: string, FileName: string, FileNameWithoutExtension: string, Directory: string, MimeType: string, IsFile: bool, IsDirectory: bool, GoalCall: goal.call, Exists: bool, Size: long, Source: string }\n  e.g. \u0060check if file.txt exists, write to %fileInfo\u0060 \u2192 Path=file.txt\n  e.g. \u0060does %path% exist, write to %result\u0060 \u2192 Path=%path%\n\n\n## save [no-cache]\n  { Path: path, Value: this? }\n  e.g. \u0060save %content% to file.txt\u0060 \u2192 Path=file.txt, Value=%content%\n  e.g. \u0060save %data% to %path\u0060 \u2192 Path=%path%, Value=%data%\n\n\n## list\n  { Path: path, Pattern: string = \u0022*\u0022, Recursive: bool = false }\n  e.g. \u0060list files in docs/, write to %files\u0060 \u2192 Path=docs/\n  e.g. \u0060list files in %dir% matching *.txt, recursive, write to %files\u0060 \u2192 Path=%dir%, Pattern=*.txt, Recursive=true\n\n\n## move [no-cache]\n  { Source: path, Destination: path, Overwrite: bool = false }\n  e.g. \u0060move file.txt to archive/file.txt\u0060 \u2192 Source=file.txt, Destination=archive/file.txt\n  e.g. \u0060move %source% to %dest%, overwrite\u0060 \u2192 Source=%source%, Destination=%dest%, Overwrite=true\n\n\n\n# builder\n\n## types\n  (no parameters)\n\n\n## app\n  { Path: string = \u0022.\u0022 }\n\n\n## steps.merge\n  { Step: this, StepFromLlm: this }\n\n\n## actions\n  (no parameters)\n\n\n## goals.save\n  { Goal: this }\n\n\n## actions.validate\n  { Actions: this? }\n\n\n## app.save\n  (no parameters)\n\n\n## goals\n  { Path: string }\n\n\n\n# error\n\n## throw [no-cache]\n  { Message: string, StatusCode: int = 500, Key: string? }\n  e.g. \u0060throw \u0027User not found\u0027\u0060 \u2192 Message=User not found\n  e.g. \u0060throw \u0027Access denied\u0027, status code 403, key \u0027Forbidden\u0027\u0060 \u2192 Message=Access denied, StatusCode=403, Key=Forbidden\n\n\n## check [no-cache]\n  { Data: this, Step: this?, Action: this }\n\n\n\n# signing\n\n## sign [no-cache]\n  { Data: this?, Contracts: list\u003Cstring\u003E?, Headers: dict\u003Cstring,object\u003E?, ExpiresInMs: int? }\n\n\n## verify [no-cache]\n  { Data: this?, Contracts: list\u003Cstring\u003E?, Headers: dict\u003Cstring,object\u003E?, TimeoutMs: long? }\n\n\n\n# event\n\n## remove [no-cache]\n  { EventId: string }\n  e.g. \u0060remove event %eventId\u0060 \u2192 EventId=%eventId%\n\n\n## skipAction [no-cache]\n  { Value: object? }\n  e.g. \u0060skip action, value = %mockResponse\u0060 \u2192 Value=%mockResponse%\n  e.g. \u0060skip action, value = {\u0022status\u0022: 200}\u0060 \u2192 Value={\u0022status\u0022: 200}\n\n\n## on [no-cache]\n  { Type: string, GoalToCall: goal.call, GoalPattern: string?, StepPattern: string?, ActionPattern: string?, IsRegex: bool = false, Priority: int = 0, Actor: this?(user|service|system) }\n  e.g. \u0060before step, call LogStep, on goal pattern \u0027Api/*\u0027\u0060 \u2192 Type=BeforeStep, GoalToCall=LogStep, GoalPattern=Api/*\n  e.g. \u0060after goal, call Cleanup\u0060 \u2192 Type=AfterGoal, GoalToCall=Cleanup\n  e.g. \u0060before action, call MockHttp, on action pattern \u0027http.*\u0027\u0060 \u2192 Type=BeforeAction, GoalToCall=MockHttp, ActionPattern=http.*\n  e.g. \u0060on before goal, call AuthCheck, on goal pattern \u0027^Admin\u0027, is regex\u0060 \u2192 Type=BeforeGoal, GoalToCall=AuthCheck, GoalPattern=^Admin, IsRegex=true\n\n\n\n# identity\n\n## get\n  { Name: string? }\n\n\n## unarchive [no-cache]\n  { Name: string }\n\n\n## setDefault [no-cache]\n  { Name: string }\n\n\n## export\n  { Name: string? }\n\n\n## create [no-cache]\n  { Name: string = \u0022default\u0022, SetAsDefault: bool = false, Provider: string? }\n\n\n## list\n  (no parameters)\n\n\n## rename [no-cache]\n  { Name: string, NewName: string }\n\n\n## archive [no-cache]\n  { Name: string, Force: bool = false }\n\n\n\n# assert\n\n## lessThan\n  { A: this?, B: this?, Message: string? }\n  e.g. \u0060assert %elapsed% less than 1000\u0060 \u2192 A=%elapsed%, B=1000\n  e.g. \u0060assert %retries% less than 5, \u0027Too many retries\u0027\u0060 \u2192 A=%retries%, B=5, Message=Too many retries\n\n\n## isFalse\n  { Value: this?, Message: string? }\n  e.g. \u0060assert %isDeleted% is false\u0060 \u2192 Value=%isDeleted%\n  e.g. \u0060assert %error% is false\u0060 \u2192 Value=%error%\n\n\n## greaterThan\n  { A: this?, B: this?, Message: string? }\n  e.g. \u0060assert %count% greater than 0\u0060 \u2192 A=%count%, B=0\n  e.g. \u0060assert %score% greater than 50, \u0027Score too low\u0027\u0060 \u2192 A=%score%, B=50, Message=Score too low\n\n\n## notEquals\n  { Expected: this?, Actual: this?, Message: string? }\n  e.g. \u0060assert %result% not equals 0\u0060 \u2192 Expected=0, Actual=%result%\n  e.g. \u0060assert %status% not equals \u0027error\u0027\u0060 \u2192 Expected=error, Actual=%status%\n\n\n## isTrue\n  { Value: this?, Message: string? }\n  e.g. \u0060assert %isActive% is true\u0060 \u2192 Value=%isActive%\n  e.g. \u0060assert %count% is true, \u0027Should be truthy\u0027\u0060 \u2192 Value=%count%, Message=Should be truthy\n\n\n## isNull\n  { Value: this?, Message: string? }\n  e.g. \u0060assert %result% is null\u0060 \u2192 Value=%result%\n  e.g. \u0060assert %deletedUser% is null, \u0027User should be deleted\u0027\u0060 \u2192 Value=%deletedUser%, Message=User should be deleted\n\n\n## contains\n  { Value: this?, Container: this?, Message: string? }\n  e.g. \u0060assert %text% contains \u0027hello\u0027\u0060 \u2192 Value=%text%, Container=hello\n  e.g. \u0060assert %list% contains 42\u0060 \u2192 Value=%list%, Container=42\n\n\n## isNotNull\n  { Value: this?, Message: string? }\n  e.g. \u0060assert %user% is not null\u0060 \u2192 Value=%user%\n  e.g. \u0060assert %response% is not null, \u0027API should return data\u0027\u0060 \u2192 Value=%response%, Message=API should return data\n\n\n## equals\n  { Expected: this?, Actual: this?, Message: string? }\n  e.g. \u0060assert %result% equals 42\u0060 \u2192 Expected=42, Actual=%result%\n  e.g. \u0060assert %name% equals \u0027Alice\u0027, \u0027Name mismatch\u0027\u0060 \u2192 Expected=Alice, Actual=%name%, Message=Name mismatch\n\n\n\n# ui\n\n## render\n  { Template: string, Parameters: list\u003Cthis\u003E?, IsFile: bool? }\n  e.g. \u0060render \u0027email.html\u0027, write to %body\u0060 \u2192 Template=email.html\n  e.g. \u0060render \u0027page.html\u0027 with title=%pageTitle%, write to %html\u0060 \u2192 Template=page.html, Parameters={title: %pageTitle%}\n  e.g. \u0060render %templateContent%, write to %result\u0060 \u2192 Template=%templateContent%\n  e.g. \u0060render file \u0027report.html\u0027, write to %output\u0060 \u2192 Template=report.html, IsFile=true\n\n\n\n# loop\n\n## foreach\n  { Collection: object?, ItemName: %var% string?, KeyName: %var% string?, Step: this }\n  e.g. \u0060foreach %items%, call ProcessItem item=%item\u0060 \u2192 Collection=%items%, ItemName=item (\u002B goal.call action)\n  e.g. \u0060foreach %files%, read file %file%, write to %content\u0060 \u2192 Collection=%files%, ItemName=file (\u002B file.read \u002B variable.set actions)\n  e.g. \u0060foreach %users%, write out %user.name\u0060 \u2192 Collection=%users%, ItemName=user (\u002B output.write action)\n\n\n\n\n\n## Type Information\n\nValid types: string, int, long, float, double, decimal, bool, datetime, time, guid, byte, bytes, list, array, dictionary, object, json, json[], actor(user|service|system), goal.call, tstring, path, identitydata\n  goal.call: { name: string, description: string, parallel: bool, parameters: list\u003Cthis\u003E }\n\n## Response Format\n\nFor each step, produce (in this order):\n1. \u0060guidance\u0060 \u2014 your reasoning: what module.action, why, any concerns\n2. \u0060actions\u0060 \u2014 the mapped actions with parameters\n3. \u0060level\u0060 \u002B \u0060confidence\u0060 \u2014 how sure you are\n4. \u0060group\u0060 (optional) \u2014 group name for related steps that should be built together\n\nLevels:\n- **high** (80-100%) \u2014 fully built, all parameters\n- **medium** (40-79%) \u2014 module/action identified, parameters uncertain\n- **low** (0-39%) \u2014 best guess\n\n## Step Grouping\n\nWhen steps are logically related and understanding one helps build the others, assign them the same \u0060group\u0060 name. If any step in a group needs the detail pass (medium/low), ALL steps in the group are sent together so the LLM sees the full flow.\n\nGroup when:\n- Steps form a multi-step pattern (e.g., read file \u2192 process \u2192 write result)\n- A condition step and its indented sub-steps are related\n- Steps share variables or data flow between them\n- Error handling spans multiple steps\n\nDo NOT group unrelated steps. Steps without a group are processed individually. Use short descriptive names: \u0022file-processing\u0022, \u0022auth-flow\u0022, \u0022data-transform\u0022, etc.\n\n## Step Modifiers\n\nThese are step-level properties, NOT actions:\n\nCache: \u0060cache for 5 minutes\u0060 \u2192 \u0060\u0022cache\u0022: {\u0022durationMs\u0022: 300000}\u0060\nCache sliding: \u0060cache for 5 minutes sliding\u0060 \u2192 \u0060\u0022cache\u0022: {\u0022durationMs\u0022: 300000, \u0022sliding\u0022: true}\u0060\n\nError handling:\n- \u0060on error ignore\u0060 \u2192 \u0060\u0022onError\u0022: {\u0022ignoreError\u0022: true}\u0060\n- \u0060on error call HandleIt\u0060 \u2192 \u0060\u0022onError\u0022: {\u0022goal\u0022: {\u0022name\u0022: \u0022HandleIt\u0022}}\u0060\n- \u0060on error retry 3 times\u0060 \u2192 \u0060\u0022onError\u0022: {\u0022retryCount\u0022: 3}\u0060\n- \u0060on error retry 3 times, then call HandleIt\u0060 \u2192 \u0060\u0022onError\u0022: {\u0022retryCount\u0022: 3, \u0022order\u0022: \u0022RetryFirst\u0022, \u0022goal\u0022: {\u0022name\u0022: \u0022HandleIt\u0022}}\u0060\n- \u0060on error call HandleIt, then retry 3 times\u0060 \u2192 \u0060\u0022onError\u0022: {\u0022retryCount\u0022: 3, \u0022order\u0022: \u0022GoalFirst\u0022, \u0022goal\u0022: {\u0022name\u0022: \u0022HandleIt\u0022}}\u0060\n\n## Example\n\nGoal:\n\u0060\u0060\u0060plang\nStart\n- call goal Greet name=\u0022world\u0022\n- read file \u0027config.json\u0027, write to %config%\n    cache for 5 minutes\n- if %config.debug% is true\n    - write out \u0022debug mode\u0022\n- foreach %config.items%, call ProcessItem item=%item%\n- call Save, on error retry 2 times, then call HandleError\n\u0060\u0060\u0060\n\nResponse:\n\u0060\u0060\u0060json\n{\n  \u0022description\u0022: \u0022Calls Greet, reads cached config, conditional debug output, iterates items, saves with retry.\u0022,\n  \u0022steps\u0022: [\n    {\n      \u0022index\u0022: 0,\n      \u0022guidance\u0022: \u0022goal.call to Greet with name parameter\u0022,\n      \u0022actions\u0022: [{\u0022module\u0022: \u0022goal\u0022, \u0022action\u0022: \u0022call\u0022, \u0022parameters\u0022: [{\u0022name\u0022: \u0022GoalName\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: {\u0022name\u0022: \u0022Greet\u0022, \u0022parameters\u0022: [{\u0022name\u0022: \u0022name\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: \u0022world\u0022, \u0022type\u0022: \u0022string\u0022}]}, \u0022type\u0022: \u0022goal.call\u0022}]}],\n      \u0022level\u0022: \u0022high\u0022, \u0022confidence\u0022: 95\n    },\n    {\n      \u0022index\u0022: 1,\n      \u0022guidance\u0022: \u0022file.read with path, cache modifier 5 min = 300000ms. Grouped with condition that uses config.\u0022,\n      \u0022actions\u0022: [{\u0022module\u0022: \u0022file\u0022, \u0022action\u0022: \u0022read\u0022, \u0022parameters\u0022: [{\u0022name\u0022: \u0022Path\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: \u0022config.json\u0022, \u0022type\u0022: \u0022path\u0022}]}, {\u0022module\u0022: \u0022variable\u0022, \u0022action\u0022: \u0022set\u0022, \u0022parameters\u0022: [{\u0022name\u0022: \u0022Name\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: \u0022%config%\u0022, \u0022type\u0022: \u0022string\u0022}, {\u0022name\u0022: \u0022Value\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: \u0022%__data__%\u0022, \u0022type\u0022: \u0022object\u0022}]}],\n      \u0022cache\u0022: {\u0022durationMs\u0022: 300000},\n      \u0022group\u0022: \u0022config-check\u0022,\n      \u0022level\u0022: \u0022high\u0022, \u0022confidence\u0022: 95\n    },\n    {\n      \u0022index\u0022: 2,\n      \u0022guidance\u0022: \u0022condition checking config.debug, sub-step below handles true case\u0022,\n      \u0022actions\u0022: [{\u0022module\u0022: \u0022condition\u0022, \u0022action\u0022: \u0022if\u0022, \u0022parameters\u0022: [{\u0022name\u0022: \u0022Left\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: \u0022%config.debug%\u0022, \u0022type\u0022: \u0022bool\u0022}, {\u0022name\u0022: \u0022Operator\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: \u0022==\u0022}, {\u0022name\u0022: \u0022Right\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: true, \u0022type\u0022: \u0022bool\u0022}]}],\n      \u0022group\u0022: \u0022config-check\u0022,\n      \u0022level\u0022: \u0022high\u0022, \u0022confidence\u0022: 90\n    },\n    {\n      \u0022index\u0022: 3,\n      \u0022guidance\u0022: \u0022output.write indented under condition \u2014 only runs if config.debug is true\u0022,\n      \u0022actions\u0022: [{\u0022module\u0022: \u0022output\u0022, \u0022action\u0022: \u0022write\u0022, \u0022parameters\u0022: [{\u0022name\u0022: \u0022Data\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: \u0022debug mode\u0022, \u0022type\u0022: \u0022string\u0022}]}],\n      \u0022group\u0022: \u0022config-check\u0022,\n      \u0022level\u0022: \u0022high\u0022, \u0022confidence\u0022: 98\n    },\n    {\n      \u0022index\u0022: 4,\n      \u0022guidance\u0022: \u0022loop.foreach iterates collection, goal.call is the loop body \u2014 two separate actions, orchestrator runs goal.call per item\u0022,\n      \u0022actions\u0022: [{\u0022module\u0022: \u0022loop\u0022, \u0022action\u0022: \u0022foreach\u0022, \u0022parameters\u0022: [{\u0022name\u0022: \u0022Collection\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: \u0022%config.items%\u0022, \u0022type\u0022: \u0022object\u0022}, {\u0022name\u0022: \u0022ItemName\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: \u0022item\u0022, \u0022type\u0022: \u0022string\u0022}]}, {\u0022module\u0022: \u0022goal\u0022, \u0022action\u0022: \u0022call\u0022, \u0022parameters\u0022: [{\u0022name\u0022: \u0022GoalName\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: {\u0022name\u0022: \u0022ProcessItem\u0022}, \u0022type\u0022: \u0022goal.call\u0022}]}],\n      \u0022level\u0022: \u0022high\u0022, \u0022confidence\u0022: 95\n    },\n    {\n      \u0022index\u0022: 5,\n      \u0022guidance\u0022: \u0022goal.call to Save with retry\u002Bgoal error handling\u0022,\n      \u0022actions\u0022: [{\u0022module\u0022: \u0022goal\u0022, \u0022action\u0022: \u0022call\u0022, \u0022parameters\u0022: [{\u0022name\u0022: \u0022GoalName\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: {\u0022name\u0022: \u0022Save\u0022}, \u0022type\u0022: \u0022goal.call\u0022}]}],\n      \u0022onError\u0022: {\u0022retryCount\u0022: 2, \u0022order\u0022: \u0022RetryFirst\u0022, \u0022goal\u0022: {\u0022name\u0022: \u0022HandleError\u0022}},\n      \u0022level\u0022: \u0022high\u0022, \u0022confidence\u0022: 95\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\u0060\u0060\u0060\n\n## Rules\n\n- Step count in response MUST match step count in goal. Comments (/) are NOT steps. \u0060on error\u0060 is part of its step, not separate.\n- Comments are documentation only \u2014 never influence action mapping.\n- Variables use \\%name\\% syntax \u2014 preserve literally.\n- \u0060write to \\%var\\%\u0060 means the user wants the result stored in a variable. Produce TWO actions: the main action (e.g., file.read) PLUS \u0060variable.set\u0060 with Name=\u0022\\%var\\%\u0022 and Value=\u0022\\%__data__\\%\u0022. The engine stores each action\u0027s result as \\%__data__\\% automatically, so the variable.set reads it.\n- NEVER use \u0060\u0022return\u0022\u0060 on actions. There is no return property. Variable assignment is always an explicit \u0060variable.set\u0060 action.\n- For \u0060goal.call\u0060: simple = \u0060{\u0022name\u0022: \u0022GoalName\u0022}\u0060, with params = \u0060{\u0022name\u0022: \u0022GoalName\u0022, \u0022parameters\u0022: [{\u0022name\u0022: \u0022key\u0022, \u0022value\u0022: \u0022val\u0022, \u0022type\u0022: \u0022string\u0022}]}\u0060.\n- Omit nullable parameters (types ending ?) when not applicable.\n- \\%variable\\% references resolve at runtime. Never pre-evaluate.\n- Literal JSON types: \u0060true\u0060/\u0060false\u0060 (boolean), numbers unquoted, strings quoted. \u0060type\u0060 field must match.\n- \u0060missingVariable\u0060 is ALWAYS a warning \u2014 variables can be set by called goals.\n- NEVER alter literal values. You are a compiler, not an editor.\n- \u0060on error\u0060 MUST produce \u0060onError\u0060 on the step. Missing onError is a build-breaking bug.\n- Actions within a step execute in order. Each action\u0027s result is available as \\%__data__\\% to the next action.\n- When a step combines a condition with another action (e.g., \u0060if X, call GoalName\u0060 or \u0060if X, set %y% = 1\u0060), produce multiple actions in the same step: \u0060condition.if\u0060 first, then the conditional action(s). The orchestrator handles running or skipping them.\n","user":"Start\n- write out \u0022hello world\u0022  \u003C= pr: {\u0022actions\u0022:[{\u0022module\u0022:\u0022output\u0022,\u0022action\u0022:\u0022write\u0022,\u0022parameters\u0022:[{\u0022name\u0022:\u0022Data\u0022,\u0022value\u0022:\u0022hello world\u0022,\u0022type\u0022:\u0022string\u0022}]}]}\n\n","response":{"description":"Writes the literal string \u0022hello world\u0022 to the output channel.","steps":[{"index":0,"guidance":"Use output.write to emit the provided literal text.","actions":[{"module":"output","action":"write","parameters":[{"name":"Data","value":"hello world","type":"string"}]}],"level":"high","confidence":99}]}},"detailPasses":[]}
